node.text: It’s been such a turbulent week for @simonebiles -- as THE most decorated gymnast in history, none of us can imagine the intense pressure Simone faces every time she steps onto the mat. I remember meeting Simone for the first time in 2016, and like so many others fell in love with her moxie and fierce determination. She was clearly shy and nervous but it’s been so wonderful to watch her come into her own and see her stand up for herself and her well-being. We're proud of you, Simone!♥️🇺🇸 #seeher #simonebiles #olympics

node.text: Earlier today, @simonebiles made a historic decision to not participate in the women’s gymnastics Olympic team finals for her emotional and mental health. Athletes—under tremendous pressure to perform—are often at risk for mental health challenges. This is a cause very near to Dona Rogers’ heart: In July 2019 her daughter Morgan died by suicide following a catastrophic injury that benched her from the @dukewlax team. Along with some of Morgan’s teammates, Dona founded @morgansmessage to end the stigma surrounding student athlete mental health. @adrianaafazioo from @katiecouricmedia spoke to Dona about their mission to ensure every athlete truly has the resources they need to succeed—both mentally and physically. #sports #athletes #mentalhealth

node.text: Today, the select committee investigating the January 6 attack on the US Capitol is holding its first meeting. This committee has been established by Congress to look into the insurrection and what led up to it.  Four police officers are giving testimony about the physical and verbal assaults they faced responding to the riot. @replizcheney (R-WY) is one of two GOP House members named to the panel by House Speaker Pelosi. This portion of our conversation almost moved me to tears. Here’s to moms everywhere! I spoke to trailblazing business leader and all-around badass Ursula Burns. When she became the CEO of @xerox in 2009, she was the first Black female CEO of a Fortune 500 company. There’s so much more to Ursula’s career and life story aside from her historic achievement, which is movingly detailed in her memoir, "Where You Are is Not Who You Are." In it, she opens up about her childhood growing up in public housing in New York City, her Catholic-school days, her marriage, and, yes, her 30-year ascent to the tippy top of Xerox’s ladder. Listen to our full conversation wherever you get your #podcasts!

More than a dozen states have enacted nearly 30 restrictive voting laws since the 2020 election, according to a June tally by the Brennan Center for Justice. President Biden gave an impassioned speech in Philidelphia today, calling the attack on voting rights “the most significant test” of American democracy since the Civil War.

During the speech, President Biden stressed the importance of passing the John Lewis Voting Rights Act, and called on Congress to repair “the damage done” by the Supreme Court’s decision to weaken the Voting Rights Act. He also criticized Republicans for opposing the For The People Act. 

"Some things in America should be simple and straightforward. Perhaps the most important of those things, the most fundamental of those things, is the right to vote. The right to vote freely... The right to vote fairly, the right to have your vote counted. The Democratic threshold is liberty. With it, anything is possible. Without it, nothing,” the President said. Did you catch the speech -- and if so, what did you think of it? Let me know! #politics #biden #vote #votingrights #news

node.text: It’s been such a turbulent week for @simonebiles -- as THE most decorated gymnast in history, none of us can imagine the intense pressure Simone faces every time she steps onto the mat. I remember meeting Simone for the first time in 2016, and like so many others fell in love with her moxie and fierce determination. She was clearly shy and nervous but it’s been so wonderful to watch her come into her own and see her stand up for herself and her well-being. We're proud of you, Simone!♥️🇺🇸 #seeher #simonebiles #olympics

node.text: Earlier today, @simonebiles made a historic decision to not participate in the women’s gymnastics Olympic team finals for her emotional and mental health. Athletes—under tremendous pressure to perform—are often at risk for mental health challenges. This is a cause very near to Dona Rogers’ heart: In July 2019 her daughter Morgan died by suicide following a catastrophic injury that benched her from the @dukewlax team. Along with some of Morgan’s teammates, Dona founded @morgansmessage to end the stigma surrounding student athlete mental health. @adrianaafazioo from @katiecouricmedia spoke to Dona about their mission to ensure every athlete truly has the resources they need to succeed—both mentally and physically. #sports #athletes #mentalhealth

node.text: Today, the select committee investigating the January 6 attack on the US Capitol is holding its first meeting. This committee has been established by Congress to look into the insurrection and what led up to it.  Four police officers are giving testimony about the physical and verbal assaults they faced responding to the riot. @replizcheney (R-WY) is one of two GOP House members named to the panel by House Speaker Pelosi. Here are some highlights from her opening statement — in which she emphasizes the responsibility of the panel to investigate the actions of former President Donald Trump on that day. Are you watching the insurrection committee hearing today? #news #breakingnews #politics

node.text: Hi everyone! This is Betty Ballantyne. We met today walking the Marginal Way in Ogunquit, Maine. We started talking and she told us she was looking for the ring her husband Roger made for her when they got married. She wore it on her right hand after he died in 2008 from kidney cancer. They were married just short of 24 years. He was the love of her life and she is heartsick that she can’t find her ring. So….I told her I would try to help. If you swipe you can see what the ring looks like. If you by ANY chance find Betty’s ring will you DM me or let me know in the comments? I am very sentimental, as is Betty, and this ring means the world to her. (She was also in Kennebunkport and Saco.) Hey, it’s worth a shot, right???? ❤️ #withthisring #Bettyneedsyourhelp #praytoSaintAnthony #fingerscrossed
